<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="25" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="25">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="25">
This species has been described from the Danube (Germany) and most probably does not occur in Iran. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Subba Rao, NV" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Survey of India, Calcutta" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" refId="B58" refString="Subba Rao, NV, 1989. Handbook Freshwater Molluscs of India. Zoological Survey of India, Calcutta, 289 pp." title="Handbook Freshwater Molluscs of India." year="1989">Subba Rao (1989)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schrank" baseAuthorityYear="1803" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="14" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lagotis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="25">Radix lagotis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="O. F. MÃ¼ller" baseAuthorityYear="1774" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="14" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="peregra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="25">Radix peregra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(syn. to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Rossmaessler" baseAuthorityYear="1835" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="14" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="labiata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="25">Radix labiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). However, recently 
<bibRefCitation author="Schniebs, K" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Conchology" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" pagination="657 - 678" refId="B53" refString="Schniebs, K, Gloeer, P, Vinarski, MV, Hundsdoerfer, AK, 2011. Intraspecific morphological and genetic variability in Radix balthica (Linnaeus 1758) (Gastropoda: Basommatophora: Lymnaeidae) with morphological comparison to other European Radix species. Journal of Conchology 40 (6): 657 - 678" title="Intraspecific morphological and genetic variability in Radix balthica (Linnaeus 1758) (Gastropoda: Basommatophora: Lymnaeidae) with morphological comparison to other European Radix species." volume="40" year="2011">Schniebs et al. (2011)</bibRefCitation>
clearly showed that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schrank" baseAuthorityYear="1803" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="14" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lagotis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="25">Radix lagotis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Rossmaessler" baseAuthorityYear="1835" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="14" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="labiata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="25">Radix labiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinct species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
